Problem Statement : Sort an Array in Ascending Order
                   Example, Input:{5, 2, 9, 1, 7}
                            Output: {1,2,5,7,9}

Approach (Brute force)âœ… Using Arrays.sort(arr);
                          Step 1: The input array is given.
                          Step 2: The built-in Timsort algorithm is applied to sort the array in ascending order.
                          Step 3: The sorted array is printed.
import java.util.Arrays;

public class SortArray {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {5, 2, 9, 1, 7};

        Arrays.sort(arr); // Sorting in ascending order

        System.out.println("Sorted Array (Ascending): " + Arrays.toString(arr));
    }
}
